					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Yeah, on top of payment processing difficulties, pre-orders can potentially be stressful for everyone and the supplier in particular, especially if a part shortage, manufacturing mishap, or any kind of unexpected issue comes up.  If 99% of the buyers are completely chill about it, the remaining 1% would more than make up for it.  Probably would be cool if there was some kind of queue people could get in, but even then you'd have to deal with people reserving a spot and then not being ready to pay when the time comes (then there's work involved with managing such a queue as well).<br /><br />It's an amazing product though, well worth the wait. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /></div>

