					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">bird333 wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Also using a Powerpak, while scrolling through the games I see a title that should be at the top of the screen at the bottom and vice versa depending on which direction I am scrolling.</div><br />Does this also occur on an original NES and a TV that has been adjusted to underscan? Because of <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Mirroring" class="postlink">NES video memory limits</a>, many games allow artifacts to remain on the top and bottom 8 pixels of the screen when scrolling, trusting that <a href="https://wiki.nesdev.com/w/index.php/Overscan" class="postlink">the bezel of an NTSC TV will cut them off</a>.</div>

